<TITLE>Fuchsia Dunlop</TITLE>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="1" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="plain_name" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="plain" TAG="plain_name" NEW="yes">Fuchsia Dunlop</REFEX>
</REF>
 is an English writer and chef 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="2" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj_rel-clause" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_who" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_who" NEW="yes">who</REFEX>
</REF>
 specialises in Chinese cuisine. 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="3" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">she</REFEX>
</REF>
 was an East Asian analyst at the BBC World Service and 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="4" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="no_case_empty" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="empty" CASE="no_case" TAG="no_case_empty" NEW="yes">_</REFEX>
</REF>
 has three books to 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="5" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj-det" PREDICTION="genitive_pronoun_him" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="genitive" TAG="genitive_pronoun_him" NEW="yes">her</REFEX>
</REF>
 name, including the autobiography Shark's Fin and Sichuan Pepper. 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="6" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">she</REFEX>
</REF>
 writes regularly on cooking and restaurants in China for Gourmet and Saveur, and for the Financial Times on such matters as Beijing's bid to translate into English the exotic names of many Chinese dishes. A fluent Mandarin speaker, 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="7" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">she</REFEX>
</REF>
 was the first occidental to train as a chef at the Sichuan Institute of Higher Cuisine in Chengdu, Sichuan, China. The author of Land of Plenty on Sichuan cuisine and Revolutionary Chinese Cookbook on Hunan cuisine, 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="8" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">she</REFEX>
</REF>
 has a considerable affection for Sichuan pepper.
</PARAGRAPH>
